The count holds — watched by every literate adult in the municipio — and in January the Party takes possession of a town hall with a leaking roof and three typewriters. What follows is the showcase: the road committee, the clinic built by faena, Nahuatl literacy brigades, the municipal books read aloud in the plaza quarterly. Poverty does not end; the *administration of poverty with clean hands* begins, and word of it walks over the sierra faster than any newspaper. The state government watches with an attention that is not friendly.

@simbolico
go-to: post_event
on-arrival: sup_peasants += 2

The campaign runs on its own legs and loses respectably; the count in two casillas would not survive daylight, and everyone files the lesson. The Montaña remains yours in everything but title — and titles, the compañeros note quietly, are what the reform was supposed to make winnable. Next time.
